                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390408-1460-offence-1 t18390408-name-1668"></join>Henry Craven</persName>, his master.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1669" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1669" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1669" type="surname" value="CRAVEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1669" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY CRAVEN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a grocer, and live in Wandsworth-road The,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183904080242"></xptr>
               <p>prisoner was my shopman—I suspected he was robbing me, and in the beginning of March I marked some money, and gave it to a neighbour to bring to my shop—the prisoner was searched for a shilling, and this tea was found on him, on the morning of the 12th of March—I have tea which exactly resembles this, and the paper it is in exactly resembles mine, but I could not say that I had lost any tea—this brush is mine—it was found in the prisoner's box.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CHAMBERS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Where was the box? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Up in his bed-room—it was locked—the key was taken from him by the officer—it is a horse-brush, but it will brush clothes—I never knew him to brush his clothes up stairs—he generally came down into the kitchen to do that—he had been in my service about twelve months.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1670" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1670" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1670" type="surname" value="BURRIDGE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1670" type="given" value="JAMES WILLIAM"></interp>JAMES WILLIAM BURRIDGE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V</hi> 160.) I was called in—I found a shilling on the prisoner, and this tea and this brush in his box.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did he give you the key of his box? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—he said nothing about the brush or the tea.</p>
               <p>
